RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 35000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHIEF ENGINEER brushed the outside of the gate at the start, was taken in hand early then reserved on the outside, went five wide while let out around the turn, was roused for more late on that bend, rallied outside while remaining on his inside lead in the stretch and closed well to get up in the final sixteenth and prevail. TREVOR BARDETTE was hustled from the gate then chased the early pace, made a bid passing the half-mile pole, vied in the two path around the turn, gained a short lead in upper stretch, dueled with ESCAPE MISSION while brushing with that foe, led under a drive into the final sixteenth but was caught while clear for the place. MAKART was hustled from the start then urged along off the pace, came out in front of a foe inside the five-eighths, dropped in late on the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, moved off the rail while shaken up in upper stretch, shifted further out inside the furlong marker, was given one flash of a left-handed crop shortly thereafter then gained under a mild-hand ride late to get the show. ESCAPE MISSION smashed through the front of the gate prior to the start but remained in the stall, was hustled to the front, showed the way under pressure to his outside, vied along the rail on the turn, dueled with the runner-up while brushing with that foe in the stretch, dropped back into the final sixteenth and weakened. PATRICK THE GREAT pressed then chased the pace on the outside, pursued the leader in the four path around the turn and tired. TIZA BROWN bobbled at the start, was urged towards the rear, went three wide on the turn, came four wide at the quarter-pole, remained on his inside lead in the stretch and failed to threaten. IGOTTAHAVEIT was taken up when MAKART came out inside the five-eighths then dropped back while the rider pulled down her goggles, went three then four wide under urging around the turn , came five wide into the stretch and was no factor. THE FIVE-EIGHTHS FRACTION WAS OMITTED DUE TO A TIMING ISSUE

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PHOEBE'S FROSTY coaxed from the gate, dueled inside of CENTAVO from the get go and narrowly showed the way under some pressure through the first turn and down the backstretch, began to shake off that rival at the three-eighths when confronted by B C GLORY DAYS to the outside, had that rival get on near even terms and spun just off the inside into upper stretch, shook off that foe digging in straightened away, then went clear holding well to the finish to prevail. KONG LOVES A FIGHT chased inside early on and then two to three wide down the backstretch and through the far turn coming under coaxing at the seven-sixteenths, went six wide into upper stretch and improved position to secure the place honors. B C GLORY DAYS came under coaxing from the gate and was forced to steady off the heels of GIRAMONTE just after the start when that foe took over the lane in front, raced three then two wide through the first turn before settling four wide down the backstretch, began to advanced four then three wide through the far turn latching on the top pair at the three-eighths, offered up a bid to be heads apart for command swinging five wide for home, then got shaken off straightened away and weakened. CENTAVO brushed the off side stall at the start, came under coaxing and dueled from the two path getting shaken off just inside three furlongs to go, spun three wide for home and tired. GIRAMONTE four then three wide through the first turn, chased two to three wide coming under coaxing half a mile from home, swung four wide into upper stretch and tired. LORD BROWNIE five then four wide through the first turn, chased five then four wide down the backstretch before tucking three wide when placed to coaxing at the seven-sixteenths, briefly raced in the two path midway on the turn before angling back out to swing six wide into upper stretch and was unable to make an impact.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: AFLEET ARLENE coaxed from the gate, showed the way in hand along the inside under pressure from DARN THAT SONG to the outside, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch and drew clear under a drive to prevail. DARN THAT SONG coaxed from the start, prompted the aforementioned foe from the outside in the two path coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, swung four wide for home, got shaken off by the top one proving no match in the stretch while running on clear for the place honors. HANDLE THE TRUTH coaxed from the gate, chased three wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, angled four to five wide into upper stretch and kept on to procure the show honors. AMERICA'S PRIDE chased five wide under a ride from three furlongs out, went six wide into upper stretch, weakened in the drive. SHEZA RAJUN CAJUN chased four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, angled five wide into upper stretch, tired. PREDETERMINED stumbled at the start, recovered to chase along the inside coming under coaxing at the seven-sixteenths, angled four wide into upper stretch and tired. MIDMON away well, chased six then five paths off the inside down the backstretch before tucking four wide through the turn, went six wide into upper stretch, trailed and was eased home to the finish. PER NEW YORK RACING COMMISSION RULING, AFLEET ARLENE WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM FIRST AND PLACED LAST. PURSE MONEY WAS RE-DISTRIBUTED

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 97. Claiming Purse 44000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRUMPS LITTLE TOTS dropped back while void of speed then angled out early, lagged well behind the rest of the field, went three to four wide around the turn, dropped inward in upper stretch, rallied in the two path into the final furlong, closed well to get the lead coming to the sixteenth-pole then moved clear under good handling. CRYPTO CASH broke out at the start, settled under some urging, saved ground around the turn, came four wide into the stretch then moved further out, gained into the final furlong, made a bid near the sixteenth-pole, had the rider lose his crop late and was outfinished while just able to get the place. COOL QUARTET was coaxed along off the pace, came under stronger encouragement in the three path around the turn, was driven five wide into the stretch, gained while remaining on his inside lead until inside the furlong marker then swapped to the proper lead, made a bid around the sixteenth-pole but was out-kicked then just missed the place while able to get the show. MY FRIENDS BEER settled off the pace, was roused four to five wide on the turn, came seven wide into the stretch, gained outside into the final furlong, chased into the final furlong and lacked the needed kick. OPTIC WAY was fractious in the gate, stalked the pace on the outside, was asked in the three path on the turn, issued a challenge at the five-sixteenths, gained the lead in the four path in upper stretch, led under a drive until just before the furlong marker then was headed and weakened. AIR SHOW was hustled from the gate, moved up to set the pace under pressure, vied inside on the turn, lost the advantage while off the rail in upper stretch and gave way. DARK STORM was last to commence, moved up under urging, chased four wide around the turn, spun six wide into the stretch and came up empty. BALLYDOOLEY (GB) was hustled from the gate, moved in while showing speed, pressed the pace down the backstretch, came up empty in the two path early on the turn and retreated.

Non-winners Of Two Races Other Than Claiming Since July 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 5 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: O'TROUBLE chased just off the inside just off the pace, advanced when given clearance near the three-eighths and took over command just outside the five-sixteenths, spun three wide for home placed to coaxing and edged clear under a drive holding clear to the finish kept to task. DURKIN'S CALL a bit tight between foes just after the start when CASH NOW tucked in front from the outside, raced six to seven paths off the inside down the backstretch until tucked inside half a mile from home, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, angled five wide into upper stretch and offered up a mild kick to secure the place honors. ALARM CLOCK three wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, angled six wide into upper stretch and weakened in the late stages while along clear for the show honors. QUICK RETURN hustled from the gate, chased along the inside just off the duel early on before advancing on the rail three furlongs out in tandem with O'TROUBLE to his outside, got shaken off by that rival and swung three to four wide into upper stretch, then weakened in the drive. YES SIR ROBERT got put in tight between foes just after the start when CASH NOW tucked over from the outside, chased five wide briefly before tipping six to seven paths off the inside down the backstretch, tucked five wide through the turn and came under coaxing at the three-eighths, went eight wide into upper stretch and weakened. LOST IN ROME chased three to four wide early on before chasing five then six wide, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, went nine wide into upper stretch and tired. CASH NOW dueled from the three path with POPPY'S PRIDE to his outside, came under coaxing at the three-eighths when overhauled on the front in tandem with his main pace rival, went seven wide for home in retreat and tired. POPPY'S PRIDE dueled from the four path with CASH NOW to his inside, got displaced in tandem from command three furlongs out, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths and faded heading seven wide into upper stretch, then tired through to the finish.

EXCELLENT TIMING went to the front, contested the pace on the outside, shook clear outside the half-mile pole, controlled the action in the three path around the turn, was asked outside the five-sixteenths, led under a drive into the final sixteenth but was caught while clear for the place. RACE.RACE_TEXT: Interborough S. AQUEDUCT RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 104. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Non-Lasix Race pursuant to 4043.2 (7)(e)(5) Lasix not permitted within 48 hours of post time. By subscription of $100 each which should accompany the nominations; $500 to pass the entry box and an additiona l $500 to start. For horses not originally nominated, a supplemental nomination payment of $500 in addition to the entry and starting fees can be made at any time prior to the closing of entries. The purse to be divided 55% to the owner of the winner, 20% to second, 12% to third, 6% to fourth, 4% to fifth and 3% divided equally amongst the remaining finishers. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a Graded sweepstake in 2022-23 allowed 2 lbs.; of a Sweepstake since May 1, 2022 allowed 4 lbs.; of two races othe r than maiden, claiming, starter or State-bred allowance since then allowed 6 lbs. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. Closed Saturday, January 7, 2023 with 16 Nominations.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BETSY BLUE five then four wide in pursuit, came under light coaxing at the seven-sixteenths, swung five wide for home, dug in under a drive steadily gaining on the leader to take command just inside the sixteenths marker, then inched away to the finish to prevail. PIECE OF MY HEART coaxed from the gate, chased three then two wide and came under coaxing when briefly along the rail three furlongs from home, angled four then three wide into upper stretch, dug in under a drive between foes from just inside the eighth to just inside the sixteenth pole and ran on to secure the place honors. MISS T TOO coaxed from the gate, led briefly clear early on before coming under pressure from FLIGHT TO SHANGHAI and SELF ISOLATION, tucked inside through the turn shaking off one rival while under pressure from SELF ISOLATION, shook off that foe with five-sixteenths to go and spun just off the inside into upper stretch, dug in under a drive under threat from a new pair of rivals, got collared just inside the sixteenth marker while fighting on to the finish. SELF ISOLATION prompted the pace three then two wide coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, angled four wide into upper stretch and weakened. FLIGHT TO SHANGHAI bobbled at the break while under hustling, prompted the leader from the outside four then three wide coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, went six to seven wide into upper stretch in retreat and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SLIP MAHONEY disputed the pace on the inside of two foes, bumped with a rival near the five-eighths, vied along the rail around the turn, came off the inside into the stretch, drifted out while battling with the runner-up near the eighth-pole, dueled gamely with that foe in the final furlong and narrowly prevailed under strong urging. CRUPI dropped well behind while completely void of speed, gained midway down the backstretch, advanced inside on the turn, came out three wide into the stretch then made a bid outside of the winner, dueled with that foe to the wire and just missed while well clear for the place. GOOD RAPPORT contested the pace between horses, was bumped on both sides near the five-eighths then pinched back, chased three wide around the turn, was driven five wide into the stretch and weakened while able to hold the show.
